The animation was based on a wargame/pen-and-paper RPG from the 80s, of the same name. BT was originally created as Jordan Weisman's house rules to add big stompy warbots to an RPG campaign that used the old 1970s Traveller rules. It's why everything is 2d6 rolls, why there is no faster-than-light communication other than FTL starships carrying information, why FTL travel is so gimped, and so on. I am reciting this list of autism because what in the 1980s became the single official Traveller setting has an intelligent species who can be thought of as wolf anthros, fanart of one of them attached. BT canonically has no intelligent alien life, or at least none known in the tiny sliver of the galaxy that humans have explored. Traveller's official setting has lots.
